---
title: Sweet Thai Chili Chicken with Zesty Rice & Roasted Green Beans
description: The pan sauce on tonight’s pork is sweeeet (and spicy). Our chefs combined sweet Thai chili sauce with ponzu, shallot, lime, and butter—a winning combination with pork filet. You’ll prep fluffy zesty rice and tender roasted green beans on the side. If this sounds like a meal fit for a restaurant-worthy night, that’s ‘cause it is (just in your PJs in the comfort of your own home!).
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6679c11e718be5f7bc5598fc-79220854.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/673d10981355715564e0cf5c-en-US.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sweet-thai-chili-chicken-673d10981355715564e0cf5c
time required: 35 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 560 kcal
  fat: 18 g
  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 62 g
  sugar: 14 g
  protein: 37 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 500 mg
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
cuisine: Southeast Asia
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1}. Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

In a small #pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add pork and sear, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{4-8%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step). Remove pan from heat.

Transfer pork to one side of a #baking sheet{}.

> Swap in chicken or salmon for pork. Cook until chicken is cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side, or cook salmon (skin sides down) until skin is crisp, 5-7 minutes, then flip and cook until cooked through, 1-2 minutes more. (Skip roasting chicken or salmon.)

Toss green beans on opposite side of #sheet{} from pork with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until pork is cooked through and green beans are browned and tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once pork is done, transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest for ~{5%minutes}. Thinly slice crosswise.

> Slice chicken crosswise (skip slicing salmon).

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for pork over medium-high heat. Add shallot; cook until softened and slightly browned, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}, @ponzu sauce{6%milliliters}, and 1/4 cup water (1/3 cup for 4 servings). Bring to a simmer and cook until slightly reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in a big squeeze of lime juice to taste. Remove pan from heat; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in lime zest and half the cilantro. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice, green beans, and pork between plates. Top pork with pan sauce. Garnish everything with remaining cilantro. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.